Claim rejection email to customer:

Good morning Augustin, 

I have proceeded in the review of your GAP claim as all documentation has been reviewed. Unfortunately, there is no eligible payout under the GAP Contract. Please see below for an explanation and details from the contract. 

When a GAP claim is completed, we compare the amount that the insurance company provides in their total loss settlement to the Canadian Black Book value of the vehicle based on the KMs. Please see below definition from your contract:

Canadian Black Book means the vehicle valuation guide used to determine the market value of the used vehicles and will be used in the event Your request a payment under the GAP Cover to assess the value of Your Vehicle.

The insurance company provided you with a settlement of $17087.00 + tax = $19645.78
The Canadian Black Book valued the vehicle at $19725.00 + tax = $22678.82

The insurance company paid you $2638.00 + tax = $3033.04 less than fair market value.

As the insurance company did not provide you with a fair market value settlement, we are required to complete the GAP calculation based on the CBB. The amount of the CBB is greater than the outstanding loan amount on the loan at the time of loss - $22216.16. If the insurance company had provided you a settlement that was in line with the fair market value of the vehicle at the time of loss, there would not be a remaining balance on the loan. 

I regret that this is the outcome of your claim. I have attached a copy of your GAP contract just in case you wanted to have a look at the terms and conditions mentioned above. Your GAP claim has now been closed.

Thank you, 

Sarah Gabor
